        "created_at": "2015-12-17T04:14:34.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Larry Link\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n Larry Link:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>George,</p>\n<p>Your green meter may need some re-calibration. Both the Potel Gaudichots and Ponsot CdlR are really badly infected by the greenie meanies; about 2 years ago a group of Bay Area burg heads went thru a bunch of 04\u2019s, and those 2 wines were a couple of the worst offenders. The nose on the Potel smelled like an ashtray, and the palate was devoid of fruit.</p>\n<p>CT notes show a similar experience, here are the latest few for the Potel, they echo my perception from the tasting we did:</p>\n<p>Tasted by tooch on 3/15/2014: Saturday Afternoon at Domaine - featuring Nebbiolo (Domaine Wine Storage - Chicago, IL): Lots of green. Thin, weedy, and dilute. (1486 views) - report issue | favorite author</p>\n<p>Tasted by acyso on 3/15/2014 &amp; rated 70 points: Saturday Fun at Domaine (Chicago, IL): 2004 rears its ugly head. Thin, green, and stemmy. No. (1242 views) - report issue | favorite author</p>\n<p>Tasted by mkbc99 on 4/16/2011: Not green, but smelled and tasted like an ashtray filled with cigarette butts\u2026reminded me of college. (2939 views) - report issue | favorite author</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I hear you on the first two TN\u2019s. The last one is a corked wine (ashtray\u2026palate devoid of fruit) and has nothing to do with vintage.</p>",
