      {
        "id": 1817983,
        "name": "Dennis Kanagie",
        "username": "Dennis_Kanagie",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/dennis_kanagie/{size}/2333_2.png",
        "created_at": "2015-12-20T16:46:56.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Stuart, don\u2019t be such a BeauneHead.   <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/3/3bd35321ffd7ed2243d1d518ebb606d554360600.gif\" width=\"50\" height=\"22\" alt=\"neener\" title=\"[neener.gif]\">   Your comment is reminiscent of the posts that started the Caymus 40th brawl in that your choice of words insinuates that anyone who enjoys a 2004 Burgundy must have limitations to their palate.  We all know that there are exceptions to the \u201cbad vintage\u201d rule.  We went through this exact exercise about 2011 Cabs.  While I\u2019m sure there are people with the palate of a yak, it can\u2019t be every single member who posted a positive vote for a particular bottle or two in this thread or the other about '04 red burgs.</p>",
